arStrings.szText: With grief there is desperation. A truth I know all too well. I have prayed to the Holy Giants to bring back those closest to my heart.
Full of grief. Trying to not give up.
My family. What Iâ€™d give to see them one last time. What one is never prepared for is the weight of loss. The way my heart churns and the intensity of memories. I can no longer bear this agony.

It is known the Beasts will answer the strongest of prayers, so I brought my strength and my broken heart. My family would do the same for me. I am hopeful that we will be reunited soon enough.  -Caonubi
